description: The ghoulish monsters and sexy seductresses known as the Darkstalkers are back! Morrigan, Demitri, Bishamon, and Donovan are joined by newcomers like Huitzil, Anakaris, and Q-Bee. It’s man VS demon, robot VS mummy, succubus VS vampire and more, as the creatures of the night battle for control of the darkness!

With Captain Picard shifted into another dimension, Commander Riker takes command of the Enterprise and negotiates with Worf's hot-tempered captors for his release. Troi tries to pick through the noise in her patient's head to unravel information on the extra-dimensional ghosts. Meanwhile, the missing Picard finds himself in a peculiar leadership role.
name: Issue 4

volume.name: Star Trek: The Next Generation: Ghosts

description:
To rescue Buck Blue's girlfriend and shut down a brain transplant operation, OMAC and Buck go after the Crime Cabal.

An undercover Global Peace Agent shows OMAC a disturbing film. Elderly members of the crime cabal are abducting young, virile men and woman, for forced brain transplants. The key figure in the operation is Fancy Freddy Sparga. OMAC is tasked with discovering the location of "The Terminal", where the crime cabal is holding all it's victims, and shutting the operation down, before it can begin. Sparga orders a hit on the Global Peace Agent, who infiltrated Sparga's operation. Sparga watches, on a video feed, as his assassin, using a missile-rifle, carries out his assignment. Thanks to Brother Eye, OMAC, and the Global Peace Agent, survive the missile detonation. Brother Eye creates two charred corpses, then solarizes the room.

As far as Sparga knows, the assassination was a success. OMAC begins his search for the Terminal, in a seedy section of Electric City. OMAC makes contact with a lowlife named Buck Blue. OMAC arrests Blue on suspicion of being a body snatcher. A sea of scum attacks OMAC, but are quickly subdued. OMAC takes Blue into custody. OMAC reports his progress to the Global Peace Agency, who stand ready to back him up. OMAC takes Blue to the estate of the notorious Godmother. After taking out the guards, OMAC, with Blue, peer through a window, into the Godmother's home. The Godmother is meeting with Sparga, who is showing her holograms of young women. Potential candidates for the Godmother's brain.

One of the women is Blue's girlfriend. As soon as the Godmother pays Sparga's fee, OMAC arrests them both. Blue confronts Sparga, over the abduction of his girlfriend. Sparga offers Blue a half million dollars for his silence. Blue, callously, considers it. OMAC angrily shoves Blue to the ground. OMAC informs Blue that because he knows where the Terminal is, the crime cabal will have Blue executed. OMAC offers Blue safety, for information. Sparga tries to kill Blue. A Global Peace Agent subdues Sparga. The Global Peace Agency takes Sparga, and the Godmother into custody. Blue agrees to tell OMAC where the Terminal is, but refuses to accompany OMAC there. OMAC, taking Blue against his will, makes plans to storm the Terminal.
name: New Bodies for Old

description: What became of the U.S.S.R.'s super-soldiers after the Soviet Union collapsed? The answer may be found in THE WINTER MEN, a thrilling 8-issue miniseries written by Brett Lewis (Bulletproof Monk) with art by John Paul Leon (Earth X, STATIC) that combines the Russian Mafia with fallen super-heroes! Kris Kalenov is a war hero turned mobbed-up rent-a-cop who spends his days drinking and taking bribes in the "New Russia." While pursuing a seemingly dead-end kidnap case, Kris comes face-to-face with his past and uncovers old secrets that may awaken these super-powered sleeping giants!
name: A Man Between Useful Seasons

description: Mister No guides a group of geologists from the University of Tokyo into the heart of the Amazon forest, for a scientific expedition. They all hang on every word of Professor Mishima as if he were their leader, and one of them has strange wounds on his chest. Who are they really?
name: Serra dos Cobras

description: Mister No’s suspicions are well-founded: his clients are not geologists, but ex-officials from the Japanese army who want to return to the base they set up ten years ago in the Amazon forest. On the base they produced bacteriological bombs to use against the United States!
name: Guerrieri Senza Tempo

description: The old secret base of the Japanese in the Serra Dos Cobras is not uninhabited. There are still some Nipponese soldiers who think the Second World War is not yet over. One of them, proud Sergeant Toshiro, will become a surprising ally of Mister No…
name: L'Ultimo Samurai

description: In Guayaquil, in Ecuador, Mister No has been beaten up for having exposed some pedlars of fake archaeological finds. Confined to a hospital bed, he tells his friend Patricia all about his adventures on the Italian front during the war and how he came into contact with the fascinating world of the ancient Etruscans…
name: Attacco Suicida

description: As the secretary of Captain Stafford, Mister No meets the beautiful young countess Claudia Sinisbaldi. But a storm is looming: some American soldiers take advantage of their free time and dedicate themselves to unlawful archaeological excavations. They are mysteriously killed…
name: Il Demone Etrusco

description: It wanders at night among the Etruscan ruins, it murders the desecrators and places in their mouths a statuette of the terrible demon Tuchulca…Who is it? A man or an infernal being? The answer will leave Mister No dumbfounded…
name: Il Bosco Sacro

description: Mister No accompanies his beautiful friend Morena De La Serna to Rio. But there is an assassin with no face in town, who kills using poisoned darts, and Jerry is the top suspect! Escaping to Morena’s house, our hero begins to investigate: what can the word “Curupi”, cried by one of the victims shortly before death, possibly mean?
name: Il Fuggiasco

description: Mister No investigates the mysterious deaths that occurred in Rio, helped by Esse-Esse and Morena. The girl puts her rich fiancé Sebastián’s house at his disposal - since Sebastián is abroad - so that Mister No can hide from the police. Together they discover that the culprit is a civilized Indio who wants to avenge the massacre of a Jivaro tribe, committed twenty years ago by a military division…
name: Giuramento di Sangue

description: Taxco: this is the ruthless Indio assassin’s name. But what is his civilian name? By this time he has reached his last victim, Morena’s father. But, as Taxco is about to kill the intended victim, Mister No and Esse-Esse arrive and discover his surprising identity...
name: Il Volto del Nemico

description: Mister No has become a co-owner of a gold concession in Serra Pelada, in the Amazons. But the place is ruled by the racketeer “Colonel” de Moura, who demands very high kickbacks from the gold miners and who is backed up by the ruthless O Bispo, an old acquaintance of Jerry’s…
name: La Miniera della Paura

description: The “Colonel” has ordered Mister No to kill his partner Zé Rodriguez, otherwise his friends Maria, Madalena and Irene will come to a bad end. But in an Indio village, Jerry finds something that will persuade the most important ally of the “Colonel” to side with him…
name: A Sangue Freddo

description: Tereza, the white daughter of the Indio witch-doctor Taiku, has disappeared: where has she ended up? Why do some freaks – a cannon woman, a dwarf, hairy or gigantic creatures - attack Mister No? What is the horrendous secret that they hide?
name: L'Orrenda Invenzione

Scooby Doo - Li See Lion - 20 pages

Professor Putter - Robot Rescue - 4 pages

The Vengeful Ghost - 1 page text story
name: Li See Lion

description: Machiko Noguchi is the only human known to have lived among the extraterrestrial hunters known as Predators -- and she's had plenty of up-close-and-personal experience with another deadly, otherworldly life form, the xenomorph Aliens, hunting the beasts alongside her Predator hosts. Machiko thought those days were long past, but now a long-lost rival clan of warlike Predators has emerged, using specially bred Aliens as weapons, and both Predators and humans are threatened. Now, Machiko must again don her Predator armor and negotiate a possible alliance with the very same race that made trophies of humans for centuries. And when you "negotiate" with Predators, there will be blood!
name: Three World War, Part Two

volume.name: Aliens vs. Predator: Three World War

description:
Explore the people and places of House of M! Wolverine carries burdens too great for even the most powerful mutants to bear. Has it caused him to finally snap? All the details you need to know about Wolverine's mysterious past and his place in House of M. Then, see Steve Rogers move from the '40s to the present day - bearing witness to a changing landscape, and watching as man becomes the minority and mutant the ruler. And in Iron Man, Tony Stark is the smartest, most successful Sapien on the planet - the best and brightest of a dying species. Does it bother him that the House of M uses the technology produced by Tony's multi-billion-dollar company to keep Sapiens down? Plus, Bruce Banner travels to the Australian outback where he's forced to save a tribe of Aborigines from a dangerous conflict between a sect of AIM and the ruling mutant government. All this, plus Deadpool is reunited with the real but very, very different Cable!

Collects Wolverine #33-35, Iron Man: House of M #1-3, Incredible Hulk #83-87, Captain America #10, Pulse #10, and Cable & Deadpool #17.
name: House Of M: Wolverine, Iron Man & Hulk

volume.name: House Of M: Wolverine, Iron Man & Hulk

description:
"Archie Gets Married: the Epilogue": The amazing events that occurred in ARCHIE issues #600 through #605 have left Archie in a daze! He doesn't know how to explain it to his friends... especially Betty and Veronica! Can he readjust to the way things used to be before he walked up Memory Lane?  
 
"Unflappable": Archie comes up with a new way to break a date with Veronica: he'll push her buttons until she breaks the date with him!   

"Career Weak": An all-week Career Fair at school has Archie leaping from job to job. If only any of them were paying gigs!
name: Archie Gets Married Epilogue: Yesterday, Today, Tomorrow

description: After being turned away from a horror movie for being underage one time too many, Bart takes matters into his own hands and sets up his own backyard movie theatre after Grampa unearths a collection of old-time horror classics. Then, after an accident at Frink Labs, Bart believes he has become invisible and sets up one of his biggest pranks ever. Also, Sergio Aragonés' regular feature 'Maggie's Crib.'
name: Bart's Invisible!; Change is Good!; Maggie's Crib; Drive-In, Driven Out; Maggie's Crib

description: Bart Simpson gets the 'indie' spirit when comic creators Gilbert Hernandez (Love and Rockets), Carol Lay (Now Endsville), and Chris Yambar (Mr. Beat) lend their unique talents to tales about 'The Boy.' Also, enjoy more of Sergio Aragonés' regular feature 'Maggie's Crib.'
name: The Sound and the Flurry; Maggie's Crib; Homer Simpson: Chick Magnet; Scared Tentless

description:
"The Chatty Charioteer": Archie goes Greek without having to join a college fraternity in this "what if" tale that imagines the teens of Riverdale in Ancient Greece! Can Archio beat Reggio in the big chariot race? Will Bettina and Veronique forever debate which of them is Archio's biggest fan? One thing's for certain - this story is one for the history books!  
 
"Let Your Hair Down": After a week of science-fact with Professor Flutesnoot, the kids are ready to enjoy the local science fiction convention... but they're not the only ones!  
 
"On the Face of It": The object of Reggie's affections is compromised... when his own beloved face gets a zit!
name: The Chatty Charioteer

volume.name: Archie's Pals 'n' Gals Double Digest Magazine

description:
Mark Millar and Steve McNiven - who last teamed for the monumental Civil War - bring us the most important Wolverine story of the 21st Century. Nobody knows what happened on the night the heroes fell. All we know is that they disappeared and evil triumphed and the bad guys have been calling the shots ever since. What happened to Wolverine is the biggest mystery of all. For 50 years, no one has heard hide nor hair from him... and in his place stands an old man called Logan. A man concerned only about his family. A man pushed to the brink by the Hulk Gang. A man forced to help an old friend - the blind archer, Hawkeye - to drive three thousand miles to secure his family's safety. Get ready for the ride of your life, Logan!

Collects Wolverine #66-72, and Wolverine Giant-Size Old Man Logan.
name: Old Man Logan

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: There is darkness looming over our two cute and mysterious girls, Hikari and Akari. Mysterious deaths are happening all around the world, with Akatsuki City at the center of the dark storm. As the well-endowed Dr. Portman suddenly begins to board at Mari’s house, Akari’s fears only continues to grow. But when the shocking truth is revealed about the strange deaths, Takeru and Ryou must decide if love can overcome everything--even if that means going against a divine power.
name: Vol. 2

description: Dynamite's Robocop series is the only sequel to the smash film any fan will ever need! Written with reverence and pure appreciation for the original film, Dynamite's Robocop - under the writing hand of Rob Williams and artist Fabiano Neves - pulls no punches and spares no criminal! This is the Robocop you've been waiting for! This issue: OCP has unleashed the biggest and baddest ED-209 yet, one that even Robocop is gonna have a hard time putting down...
name: Revolution, Part 2

description: Behind these walls everyone has their place; everyone has their job. There is no danger, there are no threats... everyone has hope. Will it last?
name: Life Among Them, Pt. 4

description: The explosive new mini-series continues!! The super hero survivors of the mysterious attacks on the Ultimate Universe are forced to deal with the damage dropped at their doorstep. But who is behind it all? There’s one person who has had just about enough with pain and suffering in life and isn’t going to take it anymore. That person is Susan Storm, the Invisible Woman…and she is going to kick somebody’s @$#. Join fan-favorite BRIAN MICHAEL BENDIS (ULTIMATE SPIDER-MAN) and rising super-star, RAFA SANDOVAL (AVENGERS: INITIATIVE) as they bring you the next mind-blowing chapter!
name: Part Two

description: This issue: "The Airlords of Han: Part 1 (of 2)!" Wilma Deering has been sent as an envoy to the city-org of Han, but she hasn't returned... and Han is causing trouble. In order to get "aboard" the hovering city-state, Buck has to ally himself with Black Barney, an air-pirate who trades regularly with the Han, but Barney is playing both sides... what could possibly go wrong? This, that, and everything, that's what!
name: Friends In High Places, Part One: What Goes Up...

description:
Collecting the complete first series in one deluxe hardcover! In SIDEKICKS, in the wake of AVENGERS DISASSEMBLED, a mysterious new group of teen super heroes appears. But who are they? Where did they come from? And what right do they have to call themselves the Young Avengers? And in FAMILY MATTERS, the newly reconfigured Young Avengers prepare to make their public debut-but first they have to face a threat more powerful than Kang the Conqueror, more dangerous than Mr. Hyde and more cunning than the Masters of Evil: their parents. For these brand-new super heroes, fighting super villains is child's play compared to maintaining their alter egos! Plus: The Young Avengers meet a familiar-looking teenage super human who just may be the key to their uncovering the truth about Wiccan's parentage and secret origin. Meanwhile, Hulkling's quest to discover the exact nature of his tie to the Avengers is interrupted when the Young Avengers finds themselves at war with one of the oldest and most powerful alien races in the Marvel Universe. And finally, discover the secret history of the Young Avengers when Jessica Jones and Kat Farrell investigate the kids' origins for a special issue of The Pulse. Who were they and what were their lives like before they met Iron Lad? And what is the future of the team without him?

Reprints Young Avengers #1-12 and Young Avengers Special.
name: Young Avengers

description: Presenting the conclusion of guest artist Joëlle Jones' flashback revealing Madame Xanadu's earliest days. Squabbles with the young immortal's sister Morganna intensify and turn bloody as the world of Fairy and Roman conquest vie for domination of pre-history Britain.
name: Broken House of Cards, Chapter Five: Curses and Conspiracies

description: The world is becoming as hot as the barrel of a spent gun, and Moses feels it most of all. Now he's making a mad play, falsely aligning himself with everyone in hopes of figuring out who killed the camp doctor before one of his new "friends" puts a bullet in his back.
name: Dry Season, Chapter Three

description:
London 1830;

Three officers of the Metropolitan Police find another officer impaled on a steel fence, it is revealed they've been chasing after a criminal for a year.

When running through the streets they see a man beating up an officer so they chase after him. He wears strange boots that enable him to take large leaps.

One officer keeps up with him, watching as he takes a row-boat flowing with electricity float into the air.

A man called a Bow Street Runner uses intimidation saying to forget what he saw, but the next night the officer sees the man again, and pursues him across the rooftops and leaps at his flying boat only to be knocked unconscious.
name: 1 (of 4)

volume.name: Captain Swing and the Electrical Pirates of Cindery Island

description:
As the rebellion makes its final stand against the Hierarchy, rival factions threaten to tear the liberation movement apart. The Irishai want the young Avatar Liana for the Warrior caste, while the Resistance want her destroyed once and for all. And Liana is still the prisoner of the Hierarchy.

Also in this issue, come celebrate A Distant Soil's birthday. In June 1991, Colleen Doran began self-publishing her epic story, and was later adopted by Image. "Empty Love" writer Steve Darnall skewers A Distant Soil in his trademark witty, urbane manner in a happy birthday salute.

The most powerful psionic in the universe is a tiny 15-year-old girl, and her Hierarchy masters will do anything to keep her in their thrall/ But a new player moves into place on Ovanan's game board of politics and intrigue. Once a lowly slave from a conquered world, will the Kimarian Prince D'mer be able to turn defeat into victory and save Liana and Earth from certain destruction? Also, featuring the conclusion of "A World for Dreaming", an original prose fiction story by Jan Strnad.

"Sometimes the Good Guys Lose" A fifteen year old girl, Liana, learns that her father is a fugitive from another world and that she is the heir to an alien religious dynasty. She could be the most powerful psychic being in the universe, but someone already sits on the otherworldly throne of Ovanan, and he is the helpless pawn of a corrupt government, a government that wants Liana dead. If Liana lives, all Earth is in danger as Ovanan will stop at nothing to destroy her. If Liana dies, the rest of the universe remains under the control of a cruel empire. But, there's a third possible fate for Liana, a fate no one has considered, and it is a future more cruel than she could possibly have imagined... This issue also features part I of a two-part original prose short story "A World for Dreaming" by Jan Strnad, acclaimed comics and animation writer! With original illustrations by Colleen Doran.
name: Sometimes the Good Guys Lose

description: Some will die...some will wish they had! The shocking story readers have been waiting almost TWO DECADES FOR! Rieken, Liana and Jason face the Hierarchy--winner takes all! Beautiful new cover paintings and 40 pages of knockout story and art! "Colleen Doran does it with aplomb, with soul, and with a sense of joy." NEIL GAIMAN The series you've heard about, WONDERED about, ALWAYS WANTED TOO TRY.

Featuring award winning fantasy author Ellen Kushner's Red Cloak, the prequel to the renowned novel, Swordspoint! Continuing the A Distant Soil saga, the stern Major Kovar, who has given up everything to aid the embattled Avatar, including his Kingdom and throne as Prince of Teramis, leads Rieken's champions Below into the dangerous depths of the Siovansin warship. Their mission: to sabotage the ship's tachyon conversion drive and prevent its return to the planet Ovanan so that the Avatar's operatives can overtake the government. But the Irishai, the mysterious residents of the world Below, have their own agenda for the destiny of Ovanan and its people. Also in this issue: Ellen Kushner's brilliant novel Swordspoint dazzled fantasy fans with its wit, elegance, and fascinating characters. Swordspoint's two most memorable characters, Richard St. Vier and his companion, Alec, the acerbic scholar, return in Red Cloak, a prequel to Swordspoint and the first story Ellen Kushner ever wrote in the world of Riverside. This prose tale is lavishly illustrated by Colleen Doran and is a must for fantasy fans!
